img_folder_abnormal = r'./data/Fold0/train/abnormal/'
img_folder_normal = r'./data/Fold0/train/normal/'
IMG_WIDTH=224
IMG_HEIGHT=224

def create_dataset(img_folder_abnormal, img_folder_normal):
    img_data_array=[]
    class_name=[]
    counter_1 = 0
    counter_2 = 0
   
    for file in os.listdir(img_folder_normal):
        image_path= os.path.join(img_folder_normal, file)
        image= cv2.imread( image_path, cv2.IMREAD_UNCHANGED)
        image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        image=cv2.resize(image, (IMG_HEIGHT, IMG_WIDTH),interpolation = cv2.INTER_CUBIC)
        image=np.array(image)
        image = image.astype('uint8')
        #image /= 255 
        img_data_array.append(image)
        class_name.append(0)
        counter_1 += 1
    
    for file in os.listdir(img_folder_abnormal):
        image_path= os.path.join(img_folder_abnormal, file)
        image= cv2.imread(image_path, cv2.IMREAD_UNCHANGED)
        image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        image=cv2.resize(image, (IMG_HEIGHT, IMG_WIDTH),interpolation = cv2.INTER_CUBIC)
        image=np.array(image)
        image = image.astype('uint8')
        #image /= 255 
        img_data_array.append(image)
        class_name.append(1)
        counter_2 += 1
    
    print("Se han almacenado {} imagenes con la etiqueta 0 -> (normal), del directorio: '{}'".
          format(counter_1, img_folder_normal))
    print("Se han almacenado {} imagenes con la etiqueta 1 -> (abnormal), del directorio: '{}'".
          format(counter_2, img_folder_abnormal))

    return np.array(img_data_array), np.array(class_name).reshape(len(class_name), 1)

X_train, y_train = create_dataset(img_folder_abnormal, img_folder_normal)


def plot_sample(X_data, y_data):
    labels = ['normal', 'abnormal']

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 5, figsize = (7,3))

    axes = axes.ravel()
    ax = 0

    for i in random.sample(range(0, len(X_data)), 10):
        axes[ax].imshow(X_data[i])
        label_index = int(y_data[i])
        axes[ax].set_title(str(i)+"."+labels[label_index], fontsize = 10)
        axes[ax].axis('off')
        ax += 1
        

    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.2)
    
plot_sample(X_train, y_train)

img_folder_abnormal_test = r'./data/Fold0/test/abnormal/'

img_folder_abnormal_valid = r'./data/Fold0/valid/abnormal/'

def plot_hist(hist):
    plt.plot(hist.history["accuracy"])
    plt.plot(hist.history["val_accuracy"])
    plt.title("model accuracy")
    plt.ylabel("accuracy")
    plt.xlabel("epoch")
    plt.legend(["train", "validation"], loc="upper left")
    plt.show()


def plot_prediction(n_epochs, mfit):
    N = n_epochs
    plt.style.use("ggplot")
    fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15,6))
    fig.suptitle('Training Loss and Accuracy')
    
    ax1.plot(np.arange(0, N), mfit.history["accuracy"], label="train")
    ax1.plot(np.arange(0, N), mfit.history["val_accuracy"], label="val")
    ax1.set_title("Accuracy")
    ax1.set_xlabel("Epoch #")
    ax1.set_ylabel("Accuracy")
    ax1.legend(loc="lower right")
    
    ax2.plot(np.arange(0, N), mfit.history["loss"], label="train")
    ax2.plot(np.arange(0, N), mfit.history["val_loss"], label="val")
    ax2.set_title("Loss")
    ax2.set_xlabel("Epoch #")
    ax2.set_ylabel("Loss")
    ax2.legend(loc="upper right")
    
def plot_conf_matrix_binary(cf_matrix, lab):
    group_names = ['True '+lab[0],'False '+lab[1],'False '+lab[0],'True '+lab[1]]

    group_counts = ["{0:0.0f}".format(value) for value in
                    cf_matrix.flatten()]

    group_percentages = ["{0:.2%}".format(value) for value in
                         cf_matrix.flatten()/np.sum(cf_matrix)]

    labels = [f"{v1}\n{v2}\n{v3}" for v1, v2, v3 in
              zip(group_names,group_counts,group_percentages)]

    labels = np.asarray(labels).reshape(2,2)

    ax = sns.heatmap(cf_matrix, annot=labels, fmt='', cmap='Blues')

    ax.set_title('Confusion Matrix\n\n');
    ax.set_xlabel('\nPredicted Values')
    ax.set_ylabel('Actual Values ');

    ax.xaxis.set_ticklabels(lab)
    ax.yaxis.set_ticklabels(lab)

    plt.show()

from keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping
from keras.callbacks import ModelCheckpoint
from keras.models import load_model

base_model = EfficientNetB0(
    input_shape=(224,224, 3), include_top=False, weights="imagenet"
)

#base_model.trainable = False
for layer in base_model.layers:
    layer.trainable = False
    
x = base_model.output
x = tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(name="avg_pool")(x)
x = tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization()(x)
x = tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.2,  name="top_dropout")(x)
x = Flatten()(x)
x = tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation="relu")(x)
x = tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5)(x)
predictions = tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation="sigmoid")(x)
model_final =tf.keras.Model(base_model.input, predictions, name="EfficientNet")
optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.RMSprop(learning_rate=1e-2)#0.0001
model_final.compile(optimizer=optimizer,loss='binary_crossentropy',metrics=['accuracy'])

es = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', mode='min', verbose=1, patience=100)
mc = ModelCheckpoint('best_model_mod.h5', monitor='val_accuracy', mode='max', verbose=1, save_best_only=True)

hist = model_final.fit(X_train, y_train,
                       epochs=200,
                       batch_size=128,
                       validation_data=(X_test, y_test),
                       verbose=2,
                       callbacks=[es, mc])

saved_model = load_model('best_model_mod.h5')

_, valid_acc = saved_model.evaluate(X_valid, y_valid, verbose=0)
_, train_acc = saved_model.evaluate(X_train, y_train, verbose=0)
_, test_acc = saved_model.evaluate(X_test, y_test, verbose=0)
print('Train: %.3f, Test: %.3f, Valid: %3f' % (train_acc, test_acc, valid_acc))

_, valid_acc = model_final.evaluate(X_valid, y_valid, verbose=0)
_, train_acc = model_final.evaluate(X_train, y_train, verbose=0)
_, test_acc = model_final.evaluate(X_test, y_test, verbose=0)
print('Train: %.3f, Test: %.3f, Valid: %3f' % (train_acc, test_acc, valid_acc))

saved_model = load_model('best_model_mod.h5')

def unfreeze_model(model):
    # We unfreeze the top 20 layers while leaving BatchNorm layers frozen
    for layer in model.layers[-20:]:
        if not isinstance(layer, layers.BatchNormalization):
            layer.trainable = True

    optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.RMSprop(learning_rate=1e-3)
    model.compile(
        optimizer=optimizer, loss="binary_crossentropy", metrics=["accuracy"]
    )


unfreeze_model(saved_model)

es = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', mode='min', verbose=1, patience=100)
mc = ModelCheckpoint('best_model_2_mod.h5', monitor='val_accuracy', mode='max', verbose=1, save_best_only=True)

hist = saved_model.fit(X_train, y_train,
                       epochs=200,
                       batch_size=128,
                       validation_data=(X_test, y_test),
                       verbose=2,
                       callbacks=[es, mc])

saved_model_2 = load_model('best_model_2_mod.h5')
